217-219 East 6th Street, north side, east of Hall Place. The large building is known as Ukrainian Hall.

June 25, 1934.

P. L: Sperr.

E. 6th Street, at the N.E. corner of Hall Place (left of center). Note the demolition of adjacent structures on either side of the corner building which bears No. 1 Hall Place and 213 E. 6th Street. At the left margin appears a corner of the Abram S. Hewitt Memorial of Cooper Union.

July 16, 1938.

P.L. Sperr
